{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-21T00:43:11.868Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Grounding in provided context"},{"type":"text","text":" is the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"most reliable way to prevent hallucinations"},{"type":"text","text":" — supplying source material and explicitly instructing the model to use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"only"},{"type":"text","text":" that material."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"The key instruction:"},{"type":"text","text":" \"Answer the following question using ONLY the information in the document above. Do not use any outside knowledge.\""}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why Grounding Works"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"The Problem"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"AI hallucinations are not random — they happen when the model is unsure and your prompt does not give it permission to say so.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Without grounding:\n- Model uses "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"outside knowledge"},{"type":"text","text":" that may be wrong\n- Model "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"guesses"},{"type":"text","text":" when uncertain\n- Model "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"fabricates information"},{"type":"text","text":" confidently\n- Model "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"hallucinates"},{"type":"text","text":" from training data"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"The Solution"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"The most reliable way to prevent hallucinations is to supply the source material and instruct the model to use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"italic"}],"text":"only"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":" that material.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"How grounding works:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Provide source"},{"type":"text","text":" — Document, article, data\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Restrict to source"},{"type":"text","text":" — No outside knowledge\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Force verification"},{"type":"text","text":" — Check against text\n4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Result"},{"type":"text","text":" — Facts from source, not hallucinations"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Grounding decreases hallucination likelihood by 41% compared to generic prompts"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Core Grounding Template"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Basic Template"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"xml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<document>\n[paste your document, article, or data here]\n</document>\n\nAnswer the following question using ONLY the information in the document above.\nDo not use any outside knowledge.\n\nIf the answer is not in the document, say:\n\"This information is not in the provided document.\""}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Enhanced Template"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"xml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<document>\n<paste document text here>\n</document>\n\nRULES:\n1. Use ONLY the information in the document above\n2. Do NOT use any outside knowledge\n3. Do NOT infer, assume, or generate beyond what is written\n4. If the answer is not in the document, say:\n   \"This information is not in the provided document.\"\n5. Only state facts that are explicitly present\n6. For numerical values, verify against original formatting\n\nThis approach is preferred to guessing."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Document-Based Quote Template"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"For strict document grounding:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"xml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<document>\n[paste document]\n</document>\n\nAnswer the question and quote the specific passage from the document\nthat supports your answer.\n\nIf no passage supports it, say so.\n\nFor each claim:\n- Provide the exact quote\n- Note the section/page number\n- Indicate confidence level"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Multi-Document Template"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"xml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<documents>\n<document index=\"1\">\n<source>Annual Report 2024</source>\n<content>\nRevenue: $5.2M\nGrowth: 15%\n</content>\n</document>\n\n<document index=\"2\">\n<source>Q3 Earnings</source>\n<content>\nRevenue grew by 10% in Q3\n</content>\n</document>\n</documents>\n\nAnswer using ONLY information from these documents.\nFor each claim, cite the document index.\n\nIf the answer is not in any document, say:\n\"This information is not in the provided documents.\""}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Grounding Techniques"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Technique 1: Explicit Instruction Framework"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"An optimized prompt should integrate: 1. Explicit Instruction Framework\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"You are an expert document analyst tasked with:\n- Extracting ONLY information explicitly present in the provided text\n- NEVER inferring, assuming, or generating content beyond what is written\n- Flagging sections where requested data appears missing or ambiguous"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key elements:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Role definition"},{"type":"text","text":" — Expert document analyst\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Explicit extraction"},{"type":"text","text":" — Only what's written\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"No inference"},{"type":"text","text":" — Never assume\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Flag gaps"},{"type":"text","text":" — Missing data"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Technique 2: Contextual Grounding Mechanisms"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Grounding the model in specific document sections decreases hallucination likelihood by 41% compared to generic prompts.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"xml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Available document content:\n{PDF_TEXT}\n\nInstructions:\n1. Analyze ONLY the text between tags\n2. If asked about information not present, respond \"Not explicitly stated\"\n3. For numerical values, verify against original formatting in section [X]\n4. Flag any sections where data is missing or ambiguous"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"41% reduction"},{"type":"text","text":" in hallucinations\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Specific sections"},{"type":"text","text":" — Grounded context\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Verify numbers"},{"type":"text","text":" — Check original\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Flag gaps"},{"type":"text","text":" — Missing data"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Technique 3: Sequential Processing Steps"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Implementing sequential processing steps enhances accuracy: This approach reduced hallucination incidents by 63% in clinical document processing trials.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Step 1: Primary Extraction"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Extract all company names mentioned in the document.\nPresent as: [\"Name\", \"Context Paragraph Number\"]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Step 2: Cross-Validation"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"For each extracted name:\n- Confirm presence in original text\n- Note any spelling variations\n- Flag potential OCR errors"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Step 3: Confidence Scoring"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Assign confidence levels (1-5) based on:\n- Text clarity\n- Contextual support\n- Document consistency"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Result:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"63% reduction"},{"type":"text","text":" in hallucinations"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Technique 4: Citation Requirement"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Prompt the model to cite where it's getting information from and flag its confidence level.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Answer the question and quote the specific passage from the document\nthat supports your answer.\n\nIf no passage supports it, say so.\n\nFor each claim:\n- Provide the exact quote\n- Note the section/page number\n- Indicate confidence level (High / Medium / Low)"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Technique 5: \"According to...\" Prompting"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"According to... prompting is the easiest of the three methods. It's rooted in the idea of guiding the model to get information from a specific source when answering your question.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What part of the brain is responsible for long-term memory,\naccording to the provided document?"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"How it works:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Guides to source"},{"type":"text","text":" — \"According to X\"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Grounds answer"},{"type":"text","text":" — From trusted source\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Reduces outside"},{"type":"text","text":" — No training data"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Technique 6: Chain of Thought Verification"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Chain of Thought Reduces Hallucination: Forcing the model to reason step by step naturally reduces hallucination because: 1. Each reasoning step anchors the next prediction to stated premises 2. The model's 'path' to the conclusion is visible and checkable 3. Errors in reasoning are easier to spot and correct.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Before answering:\n1. Identify what information you would need to answer this question accurately\n2. Note any gaps in your knowledge\n3. Check if the required information is in the document\n4. If gaps exist, say \"This isn't covered in the provided materials\"\n\nThen provide your best answer,\nflagging any parts where you're uncertain."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Anchors reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":" — To stated premises\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Visible path"},{"type":"text","text":" — Checkable\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Spot errors"},{"type":"text","text":" — Easy to correct"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Technique 7: Chain-of-Verification (CoVe)"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"The Chain-of-Verification (CoVe) prompt engineering method aims to reduce hallucinations through a verification loop. CoVe has four steps: 1. Generate an initial response 2. Generate verification questions 3. Run verification questions through LLM 4. Generate final answer using verification pairs as examples.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Step 1: Initial Response"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Question: What is the revenue growth?\nInitial Answer: 15%"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Step 2: Verification Questions"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Generate questions to verify the initial answer:\n1. What is the source document?\n2. What is the exact revenue figure?\n3. What is the growth percentage?"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Step 3: Verification"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Run verification questions:\n1. Source: Annual Report 2024\n2. Revenue: $5.2M (previous year: $4.5M)\n3. Growth: 15%"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Step 4: Final Answer"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Final Answer: 15% (verified from Annual Report 2024)"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Technique 8: Strict Grounding Rules"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Set strict grounding rules: 'Only make claims based on the provided context and evidence.' 'If data is missing, say so clearly.'\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"RULES:\n1. Only make claims based on the provided context and evidence\n2. If data is missing (e.g., an event isn't instrumented), say so clearly\n3. Do NOT use outside knowledge\n4. Do NOT infer or assume\n5. If information is absent, state: \"Not explicitly stated\""}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Technique 9: Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Use retrieval-augmented generation (RAG): Supply relevant documentation, analytics, and past experiments so the model draws from actual sources—not assumptions.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"xml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Retrieved context (from vector database):\n\"The company's revenue increased by 15% in Q3 2024.\"\n\"Operating expenses were $2.3M.\"\n\nRULE: If the context does not contain the answer, say:\n\"I don't have information about that in my sources\"\n\nDo not fall back on prior knowledge.\nDo not guess.\n\nAnswer the question using ONLY the retrieved context."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Actual sources"},{"type":"text","text":" — Not assumptions\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"No prior knowledge"},{"type":"text","text":" — Only context\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Reduces hallucination"},{"type":"text","text":" — Grounded in retrieval"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Technique 10: Role and Reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Reinforce role and reasoning: Frame the model as a product analyst. Asking why a hypothesis makes sense helps it stay logical and clear.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"You are a product analyst tasked with analyzing data.\n\nYour role:\n- Analyze ONLY the provided metrics\n- Explain why each hypothesis makes sense\n- Stay logical and clear\n- Do NOT use outside knowledge\n- If data is missing, say \"Not available in the data\"\n\nQuestion: What caused the increase in user engagement?"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Grounding Best Practices"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"1. Supply Source Material"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"The most reliable way to prevent hallucinations is to supply the source material and instruct the model to use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"italic"}],"text":"only"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":" that material.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"How:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Provide documents"},{"type":"text","text":" — Articles, data, reports\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use tags"},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"<document>"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"<content>"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Be comprehensive"},{"type":"text","text":" — Include all relevant info"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"2. Instruct \"Only Use This\""},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Instruct the model to use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"italic"}],"text":"only"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":" that material.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key phrases:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- \"Use ONLY the information in the document above\"\n- \"Do not use any outside knowledge\"\n- \"Extract ONLY information explicitly present\"\n- \"NEVER infer, assume, or generate beyond what is written\""}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"3. Add \"Not in Document\" Escape"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"If the answer is not in the document, say:\n\"This information is not in the provided document.\"\n\nIf you cannot find this information, say:\n\"This isn't covered in the provided materials\"\nrather than guessing."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"4. Require Citations"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Prompt the model to cite where it's getting information from.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"For each claim:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Exact quote"},{"type":"text","text":" — Verbatim text\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Section/page"},{"type":"text","text":" — Location\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Confidence"},{"type":"text","text":" — High/Medium/Low"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"5. Flag Confidence Levels"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"For each claim, indicate your confidence level (High / Medium / Low) and note whether this is established science or an area of ongoing research.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"For each claim:\n- Confidence: High / Medium / Low\n- Source: Document section or \"none\"\n- Citation: Exact quote or \"not available\""}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"6. Verify Numbers Separately"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"If you need specific statistics, dates, or citations, treat the AI's output as a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"italic"}],"text":"starting point"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":", not a final answer.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Workflow:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"AI identifies"},{"type":"text","text":" — What statistics to look for\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"You find"},{"type":"text","text":" — Real data from source\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"AI analyzes"},{"type":"text","text":" — Paste real data, ask analysis\n4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Never use"},{"type":"text","text":" — AI-generated stats without verification"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"7. Calibrate to Task Stakes"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Match your anti-hallucination approach to the stakes.\""}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Situation"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Approach"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Low-stakes draft (blog idea)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Don't worry much"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Medium-stakes analysis"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Add \"if uncertain, say so\" + review"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"High-stakes factual claims"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Supply source docs + verify specifics"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Legal/medical/financial"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Always have professional verify"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[masterprompting](https://masterprompting.net/learn/intermediate/avoiding-hallucinations)"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"8. Give Space to Think"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"A crucial rule to remember when prompting LLMs is to give them space to 'think'. You don't want to overly constrain the model such that it can't explore various solutions.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Balance:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Allow thinking"},{"type":"text","text":" — Chain of thought\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"But ground"},{"type":"text","text":" — Use only provided context\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Not too strict"},{"type":"text","text":" — Avoid micromanagement"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"9. Use Step-Back Prompting"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Step-Back Prompting pushes the model to 'think' at a high-level before diving directly into the task at hand, leading to higher accuracy and lower hallucination rates.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Before answering the specific question:\n1. Think about what general principles apply\n2. Identify what information would be needed\n3. Check if that information is in the document\n4. Then answer the specific question"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"10. Add Annotated Examples"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Including annotated examples significantly improves pattern recognition.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example 1:\nDocument: \"Revenue increased by 15%.\"\nQuestion: What was the revenue increase?\nAnswer: 15% (quoted: \"Revenue increased by 15%\")\n\nExample 2:\nDocument: \"Operating expenses were $2.3M.\"\nQuestion: What is the CEO's name?\nAnswer: \"This information is not in the provided document.\"\n\nNow answer:\n[Your question]"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Summary"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Grounding in provided context"},{"type":"text","text":" is the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"most reliable way to prevent hallucinations"},{"type":"text","text":" — supply source material and instruct \"only use this\":"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Core instruction:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Answer the following question using ONLY the information in the document above.\nDo not use any outside knowledge."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key statistics:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"41% reduction"},{"type":"text","text":" in hallucinations with specific grounding\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"63% reduction"},{"type":"text","text":" with sequential processing steps"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"10 grounding techniques:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Explicit instruction framework"},{"type":"text","text":" — Role, constraints\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Contextual grounding"},{"type":"text","text":" — Specific sections\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Sequential processing"},{"type":"text","text":" — Extract → Validate → Score\n4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Citation requirement"},{"type":"text","text":" — Quote + section\n5. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"According to...\" prompting"},{"type":"text","text":" — Guide to source\n6. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Chain of thought verification"},{"type":"text","text":" — Step-by-step reasoning\n7. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Chain-of-Verification (CoVe)"},{"type":"text","text":" — 4-step verification loop\n8. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Strict grounding rules"},{"type":"text","text":" — \"Only context, no outside\"\n9. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)"},{"type":"text","text":" — Actual sources\n10. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Role and reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":" — Logical, clear"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Best practices:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Supply source material"},{"type":"text","text":" — Documents, data\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Instruct \"only use this\""},{"type":"text","text":" — No outside knowledge\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Add \"not in document\" escape"},{"type":"text","text":" — Say if missing\n4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Require citations"},{"type":"text","text":" — Quote + section\n5. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Flag confidence levels"},{"type":"text","text":" — High/Medium/Low\n6. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Verify numbers separately"},{"type":"text","text":" — AI as starting point\n7. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Calibrate to stakes"},{"type":"text","text":" — Match approach to importance\n8. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Give space to think"},{"type":"text","text":" — Don't over-constrain\n9. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use step-back prompting"},{"type":"text","text":" — High-level first\n10. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Add annotated examples"},{"type":"text","text":" — Improve pattern recognition"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"The most effective anti-hallucination techniques are: (1) give the model an 'I don't know' escape hatch, (2) provide source material and instruct it to use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"italic"}],"text":"only"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":" that, and (3) verify anything high-stakes independently.\""}]}]}}
